HEADWORD: Gunflint
<hw>Gun"flint`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A sharpened flint
for the lock of a gun, to ignite the charge. It was in common use before
the introduction of percussion caps.</def> <-- used in the flintlock
-->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

